	desc = "A taut wire connected to two cable floats with inbuilt marking lights, below the surface of the water floats a large cable mesh going all the way down to the sea floor. While originally designed to keep out terrestrial sharks from public beaches, these days auqatic barriers such as this are most commonly used as cheap aquatic perimeter fencing instead."
	},
